Name: Ancient Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Angry Earth Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Corrupted Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Lost Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Coral Lash
description: "When faced wtih a shortage of steel, the Siren's crew had to get creative."

Name: Isabella's Chosen
description: "I hope you find what you are looking for."

Name: Whisper of the Wood
description: "Be as the wind flowing through the wyrdwood grove."

Name: Dark Sky
description: "When they came, they brought with them an eternal darkness. We never saw the light again."

Name: Musket of Unseen Power
description: "I did not see where the shot came from, only the aftermath."

Name: Warpwood
description: "The wood is unlike anything you've seen before, twisted by some wild magic."

Name: Axe of the Abyss
description: "Many souls are lost as they try to harness the power of Corruption. To do so is to lose oneself."

Name: Meteor Trail
description: "The fiery trail of a meteor is pure. It is powerful."

Name: Gortan's Tainted Staff
description: "Corruption has recently set in on the staff as its former master succumbed just days ago."

Name: Shield of Suppresion
description: "Tis impressive how opressive the suppresion is!"

Name: Gilded Defense
description: "A shield so beautiful it's a shame it's purpose is to become scratched and battered."

Name: Yul'kithir
description: "Demonic transcriptions cover the handle of the warhammer."

Name: Voidbringer's Rapier
description: "Let darkness into your heart and see the light."

Name: Soulforged Spear
description: "How many countless souls were stolen by this weapon and damned to a torment worse than death?"

Name: Crystalline Curse
description: "After she uttered the incantation, her lover turned to the clearest crystal anyone had seen."

Name: Voidbent Helm
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Breastplate
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Gauntlets
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Legguards
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Sabatons
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Hat
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Coat
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Grips
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Leggings
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Boots
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Wraps
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Robes
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Gloves
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Pants
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Voidbent Shoes
description: "Voidbent metal feels more durable and well made"

Name: Eternal Dusk
description: "It is only in these moments that I feel our twilight lasts forever."

Name: Guillotine
description: "The people shall have their say."

Name: Faeforged Musket
description: "The faefolk never used rifles, so its particularly peculiar that they would possess one."

Name: Inquisition
description: "We're here to investigate you for crimes against the crown. Worry not, you're already guilty of them."

Name: Longsight
description: "They say she has the eyes of a sylph, but I think she's just lucky."

Name: Veilpiercer
description: "Look beyond what is in front of you. See the evil beyond the pale."

Name: Maker's Mark
description: "As he put the finishing touches on the blade he knew his mark was out there, waiting to be hunted."

Name: Pixie's Punisher
description: "Tiny, nasty creatures, Pixies wield enchanted weapons that any creature should be frightened by."

Name: Waning Crescent
description: "Let the fires of your soul light your way in this land."

Name: Honorbound Rapier
description: "Honor above all else."

Name: Needler
description: "Sew some clothes or stitch some flesh, it's all the same to me."

Name: Faedragon's Claw
description: "If dragons ever did exist in their land, then surely this weapon is forged from one of their claws. The sheer size of such a claw speaks to the possibility."

Name: Hidden Truths
description: "Look beyond the curtain, not all is as it may seem."

Name: Frost Fairy's Gift
description: "And with a wink, she snapped her fingers. My hand grew cold, but with that feeling came the knowledge of creation."

Name: Master Cryomancer's Gauntlet
description: A magical gauntlet made for a Master Cryomancer, provided its wielder matches its potential.

Name: Torrent
description: A rain of arrows to saturate the earth.

Name: Frozen Lament
description: I cried for hours when I learned of her death.

Name: Reformation
description: Total destruction lights the path.

Name: Twilight's Fall
description: In the gauzy haze of twilight, even the mighty shall fall.

Name: Azure Ravager
description: Blazing a trail of both fire and hope.

Name: Prime Resolve
description: The primal power. The inferno. Pure destruction.

Name: Glimmering Mercy
description: Inspires the heart, and its song heals the soul.

Name: Rampant Conviction
description: Ancient magic and divine blessings, forged in the fires of vengeance.

Name: Heavensplitter
description: An odyssean spear whose form was handed down by the Ancient Guardians. Wrought from the Underworld, it is the spear that pierced the heavens.

Name: Rook's Defense
description: "I stand stalwart, a tower against the wailing, corrupted dark. I will not be moved."

Name: Boundless Ward
description: There is naught that cannot be turned aside.

Name: Vengeance Blast
description: "Your gods and heroes have no jurisdiction here."

Name: Rimelash
description: The Wanderer’s greatest triumph, the herald of Forever Winter resting in the palm of one’s hand.

Name: Legendary Azoth Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Legendary Strength Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Legendary Tech Fishing Pole
description: 2-Handed. Gathers fish from open water and fishing hotspots.

Name: Pestilence
description: "Great Axe of the First Horseman."

Name: Blessed Wildwood Life Staff
description: "Take the blessing of the wilds upon you as you venture forth, and let this staff serve both as a protector and a guide."

Name: Echo of Grace
description: "Walk in my footsteps, and I will show you my mistakes."

Name: Emberstrike
description: "Forged in the depths of Shattered Mountain, this sword appears as if it is molten lava bound together by some unknown magic."

Name: Enchanted Flame Staff
description: "Chaotic magic flows through the staff, ferociously seeking an outlet."

Name: Edengrove Marksman's Longcoat
description: A longcoat, given as a gift after fighting against the Dryads in Edengrove.

Name: Victor's Helm
description: "Only in the taste of victory can we strike at our inevitable doom."

Name: Fortuna Chestplate
description: "Rise above all slumbering souls, tell sleepless tales of journey's bold."

Name: Clamorous Vox
description: Blaze a path forward with raw power and fury to rival a hurricane.

Name: Life Breaker
description: "I have become death. The destroyer of worlds."

Name: Regent's Bow
description: "For it is the true warrior who takes up the noble cause."

Name: Cutlass Keys Slicer
description: "Death is just the beginning."

Name: Lightstorm's Protector
description: "A powerful offense relies on a strong defense."

Name: Infinity Crystal
description: "Then. Now. And evermore."

Name: Warrior's Breath
description: "The roar was deafening. We looked across the battlefield and saw her, bold and bloodied. We were afraid."

Name: Fear of Peace
description: "Assassinating a Duke is like killing anyone else. It never gets easier. For some of us, it was never hard in the first place."

Name: The Lookout
description: "There, do you see it! It looks like a living tree!"

Name: Best Wishes
description: "Sometimes the things we're looking for show up when we least expect it."

Name: Windsinger
description: "The chanting grew, rising over the mountaintops and descending upon those less fortunate. Then, I awoke from my dream."

Name: Graiths Maul
description: "Once owned by a brutish man who rarely left his cave. Known for throwing his live victims off the nearby cliff."

Name: Renaissance
description: "Take this knowledge and be reborn."

Name: Flawless Grandmaster's Spear
description: "To become a grandmaster spearman requires decades of training and dedication. When one achieves such an unparalleled feat they are given a spear crafted by the finest artisans of Aeternum."

Name: Glacial Rage
description: "Anger and vengeance burn white hot. Rage is deeper, colder. It turns your heart to ice."

Name: Boots of Stallion
description: "On a stallion shod with fire; And the winds are left behind In the speed of my desire"

Name: Hades Legguards
description: "Strive forward. He waits for you."

Name: Voidforged Harbinger
description: "Towns, cities, nations. All are yours to conquer."

Name: Cauterizing Hatchet
description: "It's not sterile, and it just may kill you. But in a pinch this hatchet will close any wound that it already opened."

Name: Opus Blade
description: "My muse sings a song of death. I simply transcribe it."

Name: Fleshwrapped Hatchet
description: “The handle is clearly wrapped in human flesh. The tension on the flesh makes you think it may not be that old...”

Name: Headguard of Valor
description: "A proper knight should wear a proper helm."

Name: Helm of the Dominator
description: "Worn by the corrupted General Gortan, his crushing control over the legions he commanded led to a mutiny that resulted in his undoing."

Name: Helm of the Forgotten Legion
description: "The Legion came from Rome centuries ago. They tried to return home time and time again, each time landing back on the shores of Aeternum."

Name: Horrific Skullcap
description: "The helmet is nothing more than the skull of some brute plated with starmetal on all sides."

Name: Warscarred Faceplate
description: "Centuries of wear and deflected strikes decorate the helmet. It is nothing if not effective,"

Name: Lion's Paw Helmet
description: "A long lost helm of an ancient batallion, the sheer ferocity of this armor is clear the moment you set eyes on it."

Name: Possessed Helmet
description: "You hear voices the moment you don the helmet. Whispering in your ear, they compel you to do awful deeds."

Name: Steelsworn Breastplate
description: "The Steelsworn smiths crafted the finest armor for only the fiercest of warriors. They did not accept coin as their payment, only the blood of the uninitiated."

Name: Enchanted Armor of the Forest Keeper
description: "The Dryads do not wear armor forged of steel. But their enchanted wood can block a blade all the same."

Name: Dragon's Breath Breastplate
description: "Forged in the fire of the dragon's flame, this dark black breastplate is decorated with intricate metal designs of the dragon from which it came."

Name: Blazing Breastplate
description: "The armor is warm to the touch, providing excquisite protection from the cold."

Name: Azoth Infused Chestpiece
description: "Built in a cave by what some would describe as a mad scientist, he used the armor to escape from his would be captors and fight his way to freedom."

Name: Iceforged Chestguard
description: "The grandmaster smiths are known for their artistry with the strangest of materials. A breastplate made of pure ice is but one of many oddities they created over the years."

Name: Commodor's Battlearmor
description: "Most high ranking naval officers prefered to wear their linens at sea for fear of drowning. The boldest among them donned their armor, prepared for battle at any moment."

Name: Royal Breastplate
description: "Made from the finest metals, this breastplate is fit for royalty. How it came into your possession is a mystery."

Name: Breastplate of Titanic Will
description: "The Titans of old bestowed this armor upon their favored champion, tasking her to destroy their enemies and all who would oppose them."

Name: Chestguard of the Fallen
description: "Lined with what initially appear to be scratches, a notch is inked on the armor for each enemy its owner has felled. "

Name: Dunecrawler's Breastplate
description: "Heavy armor is essential in battle, but in the heat of the desert it can be a death sentence. Denizens have had to adapt over the years."

Name: Armor of Unrelenting Ferocity
description: "Berserkers are notoriously picky about what weapon they'll wield, but when it comes to armor they care only that it does not get in the way of their lust for blood."

Name: Black Knight's Gauntlets
description: "Draped from head to toe in coldforged black steel, when the Black Knight rode in to town he appeared as if the spitting image of death."

Name: Enchanted Dryad Gloves
description: "What some call "gloves" are actually the severed and hollowed hands of a long dead Dryad."

Name: Grips of Fate
description: "Fate has a hold on us all."

Name: Immovable Legguards
description: "These leggings anchor you to the ground as if with magic, providing incredible stability."

Name: Monsterslayer's Leggings
description: "Aeternum plays host to dozens off atrocities. Someone needs to slay them all."

Name: Legplates of Hate's End
description: "My hatred has but one end; your death."

Name: Leggings of Unknown Origin
description: "Found in one of the many Ancient Vaults, the origins of these leggings are unknown. They seem to not be of this world."

Name: Deathwalker's Stompers
description: "Stomping on the risen dead is one of the most efficient ways to return them to death."

Name: Earthshaking Boots
description: "The ground quakes as you make your stride."

Name: Campfire Extinguishing Boots
description: "Why waste water when your boots put out the fire just as well."

Name: Boots of Heroic Sacrifices
description: "The most selfish among us are capable of the most selfless acts in moments of peril."

Name: Corruption's Crown
description: "Don this helm and become my champion."

Name: Faceguard of the Forgotten Ranger
description: "I work alone, and I'd prefer to keep it that way."

Name: Helm of Tribulation
description: "This too shall pass."

Name: Greathelm of Justice
description: "Deliver justice fairly and impartially."

Name: Wayward Wanderer's Helm
description: "Where shall we go next?"

Name: Helm of Rogue Justice
description: "Do not wait for the law. Take matters into your own hands."

Name: Hood of Dark Secrets
description: "What lies sit behind that hood?"

Name: Breastplate of Forgotten Sins
description: "For the right amount of coin, all can be forgotten."

Name: Arcanebound Breastplate
description: "Attuned to arcane magic, offering greater protection from its damaging effects."

Name: Dragonscale Chestguard
description: "The scales of a great dragon are said to be nearly impenetrable."

Name: Fur-lined Tundraguard's Armor
description: "It's cold up north. If the Corrupted don't kill you, the weather might."

Name: Reaver's Nimble Armor
description: "The Guardian Reavers move with such a calculated agility, what can we learn from them?"

Name: Chestguard of the Royal Assassin
description: "Succession can be nasty business, why not hire me to lighten the load?"

Name: Grand Watcher's Chestguard
description: "You've stood watch for half a century. What horrors have you seen?"

Name: Ogreskin Chestguard
description: "Ogres... so perfectly suited for survival and yet so dumb."

Name: Chestguard of the Seventh Hell
description: "Cold... so cold."

Name: Shining Knight's Tunic
description: "Why yes, it's me, your knight in shining armor."

Name: Chestguard-Of-Too-Many-Pockets
description: "Where else am I going to put all this junk?"

Name: Navigator's Tunic
description: "Sailors often prefer lighter armor in case their ship should run into any sort of trouble."

Name: Champion's Reinforced Gloves
description: "Go forth and bring glory to my name."

Name: Captain's Battlegloves
description: "War is hell. Do what you must to survive."

Name: Ghoulskin Gloves
description: "Fit in perfectly with other ghouls and gheists by wearing these ever so fashionable ghoulskin gloves!"

Name: Artificer's Fitted Leggings
description: “Crafted to perfection by an artificer, these leggings are exceptional.”

Name: Myrkgaardian's Legguards
description: "The Corrupted of Myrkgaard are always dressed for battle."

Name: Dungeoneer's Leggings
description: "Oh the treasures you find when you go hunting for them."

Name: Basilisk Skin Legguards
description: "Basilisks are rare creatures with skin like diamonds. They've been hunted to near extinction in Aeternum."

Name: Nimble Treads
description: "Tread quickly."

Name: Reinforced Myrmidon's Boots
description: "Guard yourself while you guard others."

Name: Critter Crushers
description: "Rabbits beware."

Name: Well Worn Traveler's Boots
description: "You've walked the entirety of the world. Perhaps it is time to rest?"

Name: Swashbuckler's Feathered Cap
description: "There's no more perfect time for a duel than the present."

Name: Cowl of Doom
description: “Unleash hell upon them.”

Name: Cultist's Ritual Hood
description: "The ceremonial garb of the cultists is as important to them as their spells."

Name: Archmage's Cap
description: "You have completed every trial we have put you through. This cap signifies your status as an Archmage."

Name: Wizardly Cap
description: "Where shall I place you?"

Name: Archbishop's Zuchetto
description: "You act in service of a holy cause."

Name: Doomspeaker's Helm
description: "The end is nigh, repent or be doomed!"

Name: Flowing Robes of Virtue
description: "Live in service of others, do not act wickedly."

Name: Vestments of Undying Loyalty
description: "Until my last breath I shall serve you."

Name: Sorcerer's Silk Tunic
description: "If you're going to cast spells, you may as well look fashionable while doing it."

Name: Bewitched Tunic
description: "Sometimes while wearing this tunic you feel as if your actions are not your own."

Name: Robe of Void Empowerment
description: "Let the powers of darkness flow through you."

Name: Lightweight Vestments
description: "It almost feels as if you're wearing nothing at all."

Name: Emperor's New Shirt
description: "You are wearing the most beautiful shirt in all the land."

Name: Elementalist's Robes
description: "Empower yourself with the elements and let the world feel your wrath."

Name: Tunic of Shamanistic Courage
description: "The shamans are brave and respectful sorcerers, championing the earth with all they do."

Name: Soulwarden's Spiritual Robes
description: "To stop the forces of corruption, we must first center ourselves."

Name: Legacy of the Magi
description: "You come from a long lineage of mages, do not dishonor what they have done."

Name: Heretic's Robes
description: "Listen to me! Listen to me! She is here!"

Name: Prophetic Gloves
description: "What will the future bring?"

Name: Enchanted Mittens
description: "Magic energy swirls around your finger tips."

Name: Spellwoven Handguards
description: "Each fiber of the cloth is magically imbued."

Name: Forgotten Ancient Leggings
description: "Ripped from the corpse of some long-dead hero, these leggings are remarkably powerful."

Name: Spellspeaker's Legguards
description: "My word is power incarnate."

Name: Leggings of Untold Power
description: "Dig deep enough and unlimited power can be yours. For a price."

Name: Silky Legguards
description: "Remarkably comfortable to wear."

Name: Magister's Ethereal Boots
description: "Existence on this plane is fleeting."

Name: Boots of Channeled Energy
description: "These boots seem to draw energy from the living things around you."

Name: Arcanist's Treads
description: "The perfect shoes for casting a powerful spell."

Name: Gold Embroidered Boots
description: "The edges of these boots are lined with flakes of gold."

Name: Spirit of Oblivion
description: "Death is just the beginning."

Name: Rage
description: "There is a clarity to it. Only people who fear it experience it blindly."

Name: Alazar's Hook
description: Rewarded for completing the quest, 'Finally, Exhale'.

Name: Syndicate Plague Doctor Mask of the Sentry
description: Syndicate Plague Doctors set out to areas of the world infested with plague, not only to aid those in need, but because plagued regions are rife with willing test subjects.

Name: Syndicate Plague Doctor Robes of the Sentry
description: Syndicate Plague Doctors set out to areas of the world infested with plague, not only to aid those in need, but because plagued regions are rife with willing test subjects.

Name: Covenant Inquisitor Hat of the Sentry
description: Covenant Inquisitors are a special branch of the Covenant. While they are relied upon to enforce the bylaws of the faction, they are also an elite force used to root out even the most corrupt heretics.

Name: Marauder Legatus Helm of the Sentry
description: Legatus is not a rank within the Marauders. It is a title given to those who have visited mayhem upon their opponents on the battlefield.

description: Legatus is not a rank within the Marauders. It is a title given to those who have visited mayhem upon their opponents on the battlefield.

description: "It was a simple message. They were coming, and they were very well prepared."

description: "Not for what is or has been, but for what is to come."

description: "While nature is quite adept at reclaiming things lost to time, it is more efficient to not lose them in the first place."

description: A carved wooden mask.

Name: Cael's Veil
description: "In each lie there may be truths, and in each truth there may be lies. The difference stops mattering after so long lived."

Name: Mask of the Demon
description: "Buried in the darkest souls, heart both burning and chilling cold, waits the demon with cunning bold."
